com.bluegosling.collections

Interface Stack<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of element in the stack
    All Superinterfaces:
    Collection<T>, Iterable<T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ConcurrentStack<E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SimpleTreiberStack, TreiberStack

    public interface Stack<T>
extends Collection<T>
    A simple stack interface. This interface is much more targeted for LIFO stacks and thus narrower than Deque or List.

      • fromList

        static <T> Stack<T> fromList(List<T> list)
        Adapts the List interface to this interface. Since lists usually have constant time append and constant time removal from the end, the end of the list is considered the top of the stack.
        Parameters:
        list - a list
        Returns:
        a stack that is backed by the given list

      • fromDeque

        static <T> Stack<T> fromDeque(Deque<T> deque)
        Adapts the Deque interface to this interface. Most operations on the stack just call through to the method of the same name on the given deque.
        Parameters:
        deque - a deque
        Returns:
        a stack that is backed by the given deque
